20 BUCKS.

13:37.550 --> 13:38.886
FOR WHAT?

13:38.886 --> 13:41.955
AN EXCHANGE OF GOODS.

13:41.955 --> 13:43.891
Ben: DRUGS?

13:43.891 --> 13:45.392
Dawn: YEAH.

13:45.392 --> 13:47.527
WHAT KIND?
ROCK.

13:47.527 --> 13:49.396
I DON'T SELL DRUGS.

13:49.396 --> 13:50.931
[ SCOFFS ]

13:50.931 --> 13:52.933
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU DON'T SELL DRUGS?

13:52.933 --> 13:57.437
I MEAN I DON'T SELL DRUGS.
I'M A PROSTITUTE.

14:01.141 --> 14:03.443
A36. SHOW US CODE 4.

14:05.913 --> 14:09.749
HOW YOU DOING?
PISTACHIO NUT, TWO CONES.

14:09.749 --> 14:11.985
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE THIS.

14:17.958 --> 14:20.393
[ SIGHING LOUDLY ]

14:24.764 --> 14:27.300
CAN I HELP YOU?

14:27.300 --> 14:29.169
WHILE YOU'RE
STANDING AROUND,

14:29.169 --> 14:31.171
THERE ARE CRIMES
BEING COMMITTED.

14:31.171 --> 14:35.075
WOULD IT MAKE YOU HAPPIER
IF WE HAD CUT THE LINE?

14:35.075 --> 14:38.178
YOU'RE WASTING
OUR TAXPAYERS' DOLLARS.

14:38.178 --> 14:40.447
MA'AM, DO YOU GET A BREAK
WHILE YOU'RE AT WORK?

14:40.447 --> 14:41.648
YES.

14:41.648 --> 14:47.487
YOU DO? YOU SEE, BECAUSE WE WORK
12-HOUR SHIFTS.

14:47.487 --> 14:51.791
12 HOURS, DEALING WITH
GANGSTERS, CRACKHEADS, RAPISTS,

14:51.791 --> 14:56.596
ALL SO THAT PEOPLE LIKE YOURSELF
CAN SLEEP BETTER AT NIGHT.

14:56.596 --> 14:58.665
NOW, JUST BECAUSE WE'RE
PEACE OFFICERS,

14:58.665 --> 15:01.234
IT DOESN'T MEAN WE ARE NOT
ENTITLED TO A BREAK,

15:01.234 --> 15:03.370
OR IN THIS CASE,
ENJOYING A COLD TREAT

15:03.370 --> 15:08.976
ON A VERY HOT DAY
JUST LIKE EVERYONE ELSE.

15:08.976 --> 15:10.210
I PAY YOUR SALARY.

15:10.210 --> 15:12.612
YOU KNOW WHAT, MA'AM?
YES, YOU DO.

15:12.612 --> 15:17.084
WHICH MEANS THAT YOU HAVE
ACTUALLY PAID FOR THIS.

15:17.084 --> 15:19.886
YOU WANT A LICK?

15:19.886 --> 15:21.888
[ SCOFFS ]

15:21.888 --> 15:23.156
[ DOG BARKS ]

15:23.156 --> 15:25.725
DID YOU SEE THE CARPET?
IT WAS NEW.

15:25.725 --> 15:27.360
WASN'T EVEN TACKED DOWN
YET.

15:27.360 --> 15:30.030
YEAH, TRYING TO HIDE
AN INCRIMINATING STAIN.

15:30.030 --> 15:32.332
HER CARDIO WAS CARRYING
THE BODY.

15:32.332 --> 15:34.567
DEAD LIFTS.
GOOD FOR THE GLUTES.

15:34.567 --> 15:36.636
THAT'S THE BOOTY.
[ LAUGHS ]

15:36.636 --> 15:40.740
AND I BET YOU 20 BUCKS
IT WAS AFTER HE DISAPPEARED.

15:40.740 --> 15:42.275
THAT'S A SUCKER'S BET.

15:42.275 --> 15:44.111
I WILL RAISE YOU $200

15:44.111 --> 15:46.479
AND BET YOU THAT THE ROAMING
CHARGES DON'T MATCH UP

15:46.479 --> 15:48.781
TO THE TIME SHE SAYS
SHE WAS IN THE CANYON.

15:48.781 --> 15:49.749
YEAH.

15:49.749 --> 15:51.084
"MY HUSBAND JUST DIED,

15:51.084 --> 15:53.253
SO I'M GONNA GO TO THE GYM
AND WORK OUT."

15:53.253 --> 15:55.655
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]
[ CHUCKLES ] I THINK THEY
CALL THAT THE EYE OF THE TIGER.

15:55.655 --> 15:57.357
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

15:57.357 --> 15:58.725
OHH.

15:58.725 --> 16:00.760
A COUPLE FRIENDS FROM RAMPART
ARE GOING OUT FOR DRINKS

16:00.760 --> 16:02.295
TO CELEBRATE
A FRIEND'S BIRTHDAY.

16:02.295 --> 16:04.197
WHAT?

16:04.197 --> 16:06.299
YOU HAVE FRIENDS?

16:06.299 --> 16:07.900
NO, NO,
I THINK IT'S A GOOD IDEA.

16:07.900 --> 16:12.172
YOU SHOULD GO, BE GOOD FOR YOU.
LONG AS YOU PUMP AND DUMP.

16:12.172 --> 16:13.773
OH, NO, NO, NO.

16:13.773 --> 16:15.842
I DON'T HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT
THAT, 'CAUSE I GAVE UP NURSING.

16:15.842 --> 16:17.710
SWITCHED TO FORMULA.

16:19.946 --> 16:22.149
YOU ARE WORSE THAN MY MOM!
[ SCOFFS ]

16:22.149 --> 16:23.316
NOW, LISTEN, HEY.

16:23.316 --> 16:25.085
A WOMAN
HAS A RIGHT TO CHOOSE

16:25.085 --> 16:27.620
WHATEVER SHE FEELS
IS BEST FOR HER.

16:27.620 --> 16:29.389
OF COURSE,
IT MAKES THE COLIC WORSE,

16:29.389 --> 16:31.491
BUT, HEY, YOU DO YOUR THING,
MISS LYDIA ADAMS.

16:31.491 --> 16:34.327
I GOT FOUR HOURS OF SLEEP
LAST NIGHT.

16:34.327 --> 16:37.497
FORMULA SITS LONGER
IN THE BABY'S STOMACH.

16:37.497 --> 16:40.033
JUST DO ME A FAVOR
AND DON'T BUY THE RECALLED STUFF

16:40.033 --> 16:41.334
WITH THE BEETLE LARVAE IN IT.

16:41.334 --> 16:43.970
WHAT ARE YOU,
A MEMBER OF THE LA LECHE LEAGUE?

16:43.970 --> 16:45.538
NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

16:45.538 --> 16:48.075
I ALREADY PAID
FOR THE FIRST ONE.
[ SIGHS ]

16:48.075 --> 16:51.744
WELL, YOU CAN TELL THE STATE OF
CALIFORNIA THEY CAN KISS MY ASS!

16:51.744 --> 16:54.347
[ SIGHS ]

16:54.347 --> 16:58.718
OHH. I GOT TO PAY
FOR ANOTHER CUSTODY EVALUATION.

16:58.718 --> 17:01.288
TAMMI'S SUCKING
MY BANK ACCOUNT DRY.

17:01.288 --> 17:03.523
SHE'S PUSHING ME
FURTHER IN DEBT.

17:03.523 --> 17:06.259
YOU EVER THINK ABOUT GETTING
YOUR GUARD CARD?

17:06.259 --> 17:09.762
I HEAR TARGET'S HIRING
FOR THEIR EASTER SALE.

17:09.762 --> 17:12.399
HOW ABOUT I GET A LOAN
FROM YOUR FOLKS?

17:12.399 --> 17:13.500
OH.

17:13.500 --> 17:16.469
THE AIR'S NOT WORKING RIGHT.
IT'S HOT, MAN.

17:18.605 --> 17:20.540
Sammy:
WHAT ARE WE DOING HERE?

17:20.540 --> 17:23.643
UH, JUST PASSING ON THROUGH,
SEE IF ANYTHING'S GOING ON.

17:23.643 --> 17:25.812
WAIT A SECOND.
HERE WE GO.

17:25.812 --> 17:29.549
THERE WAS NO CONFIRMATION
THAT IT WAS THE EASTSIDE G's.

17:29.549 --> 17:32.752
YEAH. OUR PAL DEWAIN'S GOT
A BENCH WARRANT.

17:32.752 --> 17:34.020
IT'S A LEGIT STOP.

17:34.020 --> 17:35.922
HEY, BEN!

17:35.922 --> 17:37.624
HEY, DEWAIN!

17:37.624 --> 17:39.126
YO, DEWAIN!

17:39.126 --> 17:40.893
[ LAUGHING ]

17:40.893 --> 17:43.230
YO, WHAT'S UP, MAN?

17:43.230 --> 17:45.432
WE DIDN'T GET THE INVITE.

17:45.432 --> 17:47.267
IT'S MY SON'S
BIRTHDAY PARTY.

17:47.267 --> 17:48.568
YEAH,
I CAN SEE THAT.

17:48.568 --> 17:50.570
THIS'LL
JUST TAKE A MINUTE.

17:53.072 --> 17:54.274
HOW YOU DOING?

17:54.274 --> 17:57.544
[ INDISTINCT WHISPERING ]

17:57.544 --> 18:00.147
[ SNIFFS ]

18:00.147 --> 18:02.081
[ SMACKS LIPS ]

18:02.081 --> 18:04.284
SO, LOOK.

18:04.284 --> 18:05.685
A FRIEND OF OURS GOT SHOT.

18:05.685 --> 18:08.888
WORD IS SOMEONE
FROM YOUR CLIQUE DID IT.

18:08.888 --> 18:10.890
HE ALIVE?

18:10.890 --> 18:11.958
YEAH.

18:11.958 --> 18:13.626
WE DIDN'T DO IT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:13.626 --> 18:16.663
EASTSIDE G's
HAVE BEEN GETTING BOLDER.

18:16.663 --> 18:19.499
EVERYBODY KNOWS YOU GOT BEEF
WITH OUR GANG GUYS.

18:21.234 --> 18:23.069
I'VE GOT A WARRANT, DEWAIN.

18:23.069 --> 18:25.205
YOU MISSED
A COURT APPEARANCE.

18:25.205 --> 18:26.506
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

18:26.506 --> 18:29.442
I WAS LOCKED UP
WHEN MY SON WAS BORN.

18:29.442 --> 18:31.144
IT'S THE FIRST BIRTHDAY
I'M AROUND, MAN.

18:31.144 --> 18:33.913
YOU GIVE US WHAT WE NEED, WE'LL
LET YOU GO BACK TO YOUR PARTY.

18:33.913 --> 18:35.248
COME ON, DAWG.

18:35.248 --> 18:36.949
HEY, I WOULD HATE FOR YOU
TO MISS THE CAKE.

18:36.949 --> 18:40.620
YOUR LITTLE BOY BLOWING OUT
THE CANDLES, MAKING A WISH.

18:40.620 --> 18:42.922
ALL RIGHT, LOOK.
FINE. FINE. LOOK.

18:42.922 --> 18:46.559
I HEARD THAT LARON...

18:46.559 --> 18:49.429
TALKIN' SHIT
ABOUT BLASTIN' ON FIVE-O's.

18:49.429 --> 18:52.265
LARON, FROM TWO-TREYS?

18:52.265 --> 18:55.101
YOUR RIVAL GANG?

18:55.101 --> 18:56.969
WHAT?
YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME?

18:56.969 --> 18:57.904
NO.

18:57.904 --> 18:59.439
FUCK YOU.

19:01.908 --> 19:03.676
FINE,
I PUT IT ON MY MAMA.

19:03.676 --> 19:04.877
COME ON, DEWAIN.

19:04.877 --> 19:07.447
EVERYBODY IN SOUTH CENTRAL
KNOWS YOU HATE YOUR MAMA.

19:09.249 --> 19:12.185
YOU PUT IT ON YOUR SON?

19:18.291 --> 19:20.827
FINE, MAN.

19:20.827 --> 19:22.729
I PUT THAT ON MY SON.

19:22.729 --> 19:24.364
[ DOG BARKING ]

19:28.335 --> 19:31.204
HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO HIM.

19:31.204 --> 19:33.306
HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU,
MOTHERFUCKER.

19:34.641 --> 19:36.476
WHAT'S THIS?

19:36.476 --> 19:41.448
THERE WE GO. THERE WE GO.
RIGHT THERE.

19:42.915 --> 19:45.252
Ben: HEY, LARON.

19:45.252 --> 19:48.455
WE NEED A WORD.
HOW YOU DOING, MAN?

19:48.455 --> 19:50.790
WHERE YOU GOING?
HEY! HEY!

19:57.063 --> 19:59.399
[ PANTING ]

20:03.903 --> 20:06.406
Shit.

20:12.178 --> 20:15.348
HE'S HEADING
IN THE COURTYARD.

20:21.821 --> 20:23.556
[ DOG BARKING ]

20:26.192 --> 20:28.961
SAMMY:
Sherman, can you hear me?

20:33.132 --> 20:34.967
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

20:39.706 --> 20:43.175
WHERE THE FUCK
DID YOU GO?

20:43.175 --> 20:45.678
[ BARKING CONTINUES ]

20:57.924 --> 21:00.327
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

21:03.930 --> 21:05.398
[ CLATTER IN DISTANCE ]

21:05.398 --> 21:06.866
HEY! HEY!

21:07.734 --> 21:09.536
ALL RIGHT.
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

21:09.536 --> 21:11.137
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT. YOU'RE
ALL RIGHT. YOU'RE OKAY.

21:11.137 --> 21:12.972
Shit.

21:15.241 --> 21:16.876
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

21:18.545 --> 21:21.748
GET OVER HERE!
GET DOWN! GET DOWN!

21:21.748 --> 21:24.150
[ GRUNTING ]

21:24.150 --> 21:25.385
[ PANTING ]

21:25.385 --> 21:27.787
POLICE BRUTALITY TYPES.

21:27.787 --> 21:28.421
YEAH.

21:28.421 --> 21:29.822
ALL RIGHT.

21:29.822 --> 21:30.723
ROLL OVER.

21:30.723 --> 21:32.792
ROLL OVER. ROLL OVER.
SIT UP.

21:32.792 --> 21:35.662
THERE YOU GO.
YOU KNOW THE DRILL.

21:35.662 --> 21:37.096
OH! TAKE IT EASY, MAN!

21:37.096 --> 21:38.531
WELL, YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE BEEN
RUNNING, LARON.

21:38.531 --> 21:40.299
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE BEEN
RUNNING.

21:40.299 --> 21:41.401
LOOK WHAT I GOT.

21:41.401 --> 21:42.602
Laron: WHAT?
THAT'S JUST A KIBBLE.

21:42.602 --> 21:44.036
YOU GONNA FUCK ME OVER
FOR THAT?

21:44.036 --> 21:46.305
NAH, WE DON'T GIVE A SHIT
ABOUT THE KIBBLE.

21:46.305 --> 21:48.040
IT'S THE OTHER THING.

21:48.040 --> 21:49.376
WHAT SHIT?

21:49.376 --> 21:50.610
YOU KNOW.

21:50.610 --> 21:54.046
SOMEBODY GOT A BEEF ON ME,
MAN?

21:54.046 --> 21:56.716
IS IT THAT BITCH ANGIE?

21:56.716 --> 21:59.419
THINK I'M STEPPING OUT ON HER,
DAWG.

22:03.890 --> 22:05.191
EASTSIDE G's?

22:05.191 --> 22:06.859
YO --

22:06.859 --> 22:09.996
LARON, I WOULDN'T START RUNNING
YOUR MOUTH WITHOUT A LAWYER.

22:09.996 --> 22:12.899
YO.

22:12.899 --> 22:14.601
WAS IT DEWAIN?

22:14.601 --> 22:17.136
ASSHOLE THINK I'M FUCKING
HIS SISTER, MAN.

22:17.136 --> 22:19.171
WAS IT?
[ LAUGHS ]

22:19.171 --> 22:20.973
Laron:
THAT MOTHERFUCKER.

22:20.973 --> 22:23.342
GET IN THE FUCKING CAR.
GET IN THE CAR.
GET IN THE CAR.

22:23.342 --> 22:24.944
TELL DEWAIN
I WANT TO SEE HIS FUCK --

22:24.944 --> 22:27.480
REALLY?

22:27.480 --> 22:30.082
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

22:32.284 --> 22:34.421
Lydia: ALL RIGHT.

22:34.421 --> 22:37.490
OKAY, THANKS.

22:37.490 --> 22:39.091
WELL,
CORONER'S REPORT CONFIRMED

22:39.091 --> 22:42.094
THAT RICK DAWSON DIED
FROM A HEAD CONTUSION.

22:42.094 --> 22:45.965
ANN MUST HAVE DUMPED THE BODY
AND THEN SET IT ON FIRE.

22:45.965 --> 22:47.767
MAMA SAID KNOCK YOU OUT.

22:51.103 --> 22:53.540
YOU'RE SERIOUSLY GONNA EAT
SOME SOUP IN THIS HEAT?

22:53.540 --> 22:56.242
YEAH. I STILL GOT
BABY WEIGHT TO LOSE.

22:56.242 --> 22:57.910
WHAT?
NO. NO, NO, NO, NO.

22:57.910 --> 23:00.980
DON'T BE SO HARD ON YOURSELF.
YOU LOOK GOOD.

23:00.980 --> 23:02.114
THANK YOU.

23:02.114 --> 23:04.551
BUT IT IS GONNA BE TOUGH
LOSING THESE LAST POUNDS

23:04.551 --> 23:06.152
NOW THAT I STOPPED NURSING.

23:06.152 --> 23:09.722
SHOOT. MY WIFE IS STILL
TRYING TO LOSE HER BABY WEIGHT.

23:09.722 --> 23:12.191
MY LAST KID
WAS SEVEN YEARS AGO.

23:12.191 --> 23:15.728
AND I'M SURE SHE REALLY
APPRECIATES YOU SAYING THAT.

23:18.598 --> 23:20.032
HOW'S CHRISTOPHER? HMM?

23:20.032 --> 23:21.834
THINGS BETTER AT HOME?

23:21.834 --> 23:24.671
COMING TO WORK IS
THE EASY PART OF MY DAY.

23:24.671 --> 23:27.907
I'D TAKE DEAD BODIES
OVER A SCREAMING BABY ANYTIME.

23:27.907 --> 23:29.609
OH, YEAH.
THEY BOTH STINK.

23:29.609 --> 23:31.444
AT LEAST THE BODIES
ARE QUIET.

23:31.444 --> 23:32.712
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:36.683 --> 23:39.085
YOU GETTING ANY HELP
FROM ANYONE ELSE AT HOME,

23:39.085 --> 23:41.087
BESIDES YOUR MOM'S?

23:41.087 --> 23:45.024
I KNOW BEING A SINGLE MOM'S
KINDA TOUGH.

23:45.024 --> 23:48.728
LIKE WHO?
THE BABY'S DADDY?

23:48.728 --> 23:50.930
DON'T GO THERE.

23:53.566 --> 23:55.702
MMM,
THIS PASTRAMI IS JUST...

23:55.702 --> 23:56.836
IT'S DELICIOUS.

23:56.836 --> 24:00.039
MAKE YOU WANT TO SMACK
YOUR MAMA.

24:05.111 --> 24:07.246
WANT TO TAKE A PICTURE
WITH ME?

24:07.246 --> 24:11.250
NO, THANKS. YOUR MUG
WILL GIVE NATE NIGHTMARES.

24:11.250 --> 24:15.121
GUYS, I NEED A WORD.

24:18.658 --> 24:23.329
MENDOZA LIED,
MADE UP THE ENTIRE STORY.

24:23.329 --> 24:25.598
HE GOT SHOT.

24:25.598 --> 24:27.066
IT WAS SELF-INFLICTED.

24:27.066 --> 24:29.235
HE WAS UNDERWATER
ON HIS BILLS,

24:29.235 --> 24:32.805
TRYING TO COLLECT
ON THE INSURANCE MONEY.

24:32.805 --> 24:35.341
WHAT A WASTE
OF RESOURCES.

24:35.341 --> 24:36.976
PRESS IS GONNA HAVE
A FIELD DAY.

24:36.976 --> 24:38.945
IT'S GONNA BE
A REAL CLUSTERFUCK.

24:38.945 --> 24:41.748
MEDIA RELATIONS IS TRYING
TO FIGURE OUT HOW TO SPIN THIS.

24:41.748 --> 24:42.982
YOU NEED US
TO DO ANYTHING?

24:42.982 --> 24:44.350
NO. NO.
JUST KEEP IT UNDER YOUR HATS.

24:44.350 --> 24:46.152
WE HAVEN'T TOLD
THE REST OF THE DIVISION YET.

24:46.152 --> 24:49.822
SHERMAN,
I KNOW YOU TWO WERE CLOSE.

24:49.822 --> 24:51.991
YOU WENT OUT ON A LIMB
FOR HIM.

24:51.991 --> 24:54.493
WANT TO MAKE SURE
YOU'RE OKAY.

24:55.828 --> 24:59.131
GUESS I GOT TO CANCEL
THE BARBECUE.

24:59.131 --> 25:00.967
EXCUSE ME.

25:04.436 --> 25:06.205
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

25:06.205 --> 25:07.540
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

25:07.540 --> 25:10.376
THINGS AREN'T LOOKING TOO GOOD
FOR OUR BOXING CHAMP.

25:10.376 --> 25:11.510
HMM.

25:11.510 --> 25:13.112
THE PHONE COMPANY
HAS NO RECORD

25:13.112 --> 25:15.615
OF HER ALLEGED PHONE CALLS
TO CHECK ON HIM.

25:15.615 --> 25:16.983
OH, SHOCKER.

25:16.983 --> 25:18.284
MM-HMM.

25:18.284 --> 25:20.920
AND LIKE YOU SAID, THE ROAMING
SIGNALS DO NOT MATCH UP

25:20.920 --> 25:23.790
TO THE TIME SHE SAID SHE WAS
IN THE CANYON BECAUSE...

25:23.790 --> 25:25.758
HER PHONE WAS OFF
FOR 13 HOURS.

25:25.758 --> 25:28.527
[ As ring announcer ]
LYDIA "THE BLACK STALLION" ADAMS

25:28.527 --> 25:29.929
DELIVERS A STAGGERING BLOW

25:29.929 --> 25:32.198
TO ANN "THE MAN-EATER"
DAWSON'S STORY.

25:32.198 --> 25:34.200
SHE REPORTED HIM MISSING
THE NEXT DAY,

25:34.200 --> 25:37.203
A COUPLE OF HOURS AFTER
SHE TURNED HER PHONE BACK ON.

25:37.203 --> 25:39.471
OH, ADAMS HAS GOT DAWSON
AGAINST THE ROPES.

25:39.471 --> 25:42.241
CREDIT CARD HISTORY SHOWS
THAT SHE BOUGHT THE CARPET

25:42.241 --> 25:45.144
THE NEXT DAY
AFTER RICK DISAPPEARED.

25:45.144 --> 25:46.478
[ EXHALING SHARPLY ]

25:46.478 --> 25:49.215
SHE KILLED HIM IN HER OFFICE,
COVERED UP THE BLOOD,

25:49.215 --> 25:51.150
DUMPED THE BODY
IN THE CANYON.

25:51.150 --> 25:52.952
OH! IT'S A KNOCK-OUT!

25:52.952 --> 25:54.987
[ IMITATES CROWD ROARING,
CHUCKLES ]
SHE'S THE CHAMPION!

25:54.987 --> 25:57.790
YOU'RE PRETTY! YOU AIN'T GOT
A SCRATCH ON YOUR FACE!

25:57.790 --> 26:00.392
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

26:00.392 --> 26:03.162
CIRCLE JERK OF A DAY,
HUH?

26:03.162 --> 26:05.898
DISPATCHER:
Any available unit to handle,

26:05.898 --> 26:09.501
we have shots fired
in the 400 block of 65th Street.

26:09.501 --> 26:13.572
Stand by for additional info.
Unit to handle, identify.

26:13.572 --> 26:14.941
THAT'S DEWAIN'S PAD.

26:14.941 --> 26:17.309
LARON MUST HAVE MADE
HIS ONE PHONE CALL.

26:17.309 --> 26:19.445
A36, SHOW US RESPONDING.

26:19.445 --> 26:21.180
[ SIREN WAILING ]

26:32.725 --> 26:34.927
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

26:39.131 --> 26:41.934
[ GROANING ]

26:43.402 --> 26:45.004
COME ON, MAN.

26:47.740 --> 26:49.842
[ WHEEZING ]

26:50.710 --> 26:52.712
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.

26:52.712 --> 26:54.280
LOOK AT THIS.

26:54.280 --> 26:56.282
STAY BACK.
STAY BACK. STAY BACK.

26:56.282 --> 26:57.616
THE FUCK?

26:57.616 --> 27:00.753
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.
CLEAR A LANE! CLEAR A LANE!

27:00.753 --> 27:02.488
WE GOT TO GET THE AMBULANCE
IN HERE, MAN.

27:02.488 --> 27:03.656
[ HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING ]

27:03.656 --> 27:06.592
[ CRYING ]

27:06.592 --> 27:09.495
COME ON.

27:09.495 --> 27:10.697
[ SHOUTING CONTINUES ]

27:13.399 --> 27:14.734
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

27:14.734 --> 27:17.036
HELP IS ON THE WAY.
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

27:17.036 --> 27:18.671
COME ON.

27:20.206 --> 27:22.742
[ PUNCHES LANDING
ON PUNCHING BAG ]

27:26.345 --> 27:28.414
ANN DAWSON.

27:28.414 --> 27:29.882
DETECTIVES.

27:32.051 --> 27:34.754
DO YOU MIND IF WE TAKE A LOOK
IN YOUR OFFICE?

27:34.754 --> 27:37.223
YEAH, I, UH -- I DO.

27:38.858 --> 27:40.893
YEAH,
I THOUGHT YOU'D SAY THAT.

27:40.893 --> 27:42.795
WE HAVE A WARRANT.

27:45.664 --> 27:46.966
OH!

28:01.347 --> 28:03.049
STOP!

28:07.854 --> 28:10.790
[ GRUNTS ]

28:10.790 --> 28:12.324
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

28:15.227 --> 28:16.228
LET GO OF ME!

28:23.736 --> 28:24.904
[ COUGHS ]

28:24.904 --> 28:26.272
STAY DOWN!

28:26.272 --> 28:27.706
[ GRUNTING ]

28:27.706 --> 28:29.275
STAY THERE!

28:29.275 --> 28:31.610
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

28:31.610 --> 28:33.846
[ GROANS ]

28:39.418 --> 28:41.888
[ COUGHS ]

28:46.592 --> 28:49.495
[ GASPING ]

28:50.696 --> 28:51.798
Ruben: LYDIA!

28:51.798 --> 28:53.365
[ PANTING ]

28:54.934 --> 28:56.268
YOU ALL RIGHT?

29:04.276 --> 29:05.945
[ SPITS ]

29:05.945 --> 29:07.780
YEAH, PARTNER.

29:07.780 --> 29:10.783
DON'T CALL IT A COMEBACK.

29:16.956 --> 29:20.426
THEY DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S GOING TO HAPPEN TO HIM.

29:23.930 --> 29:27.800
I SHOULD HAVE KEPT
MY MOUTH SHUT.

29:33.405 --> 29:35.274
[ CRYING ]

29:44.583 --> 29:46.218
THANKS FOR COMING, OFFICERS.

29:46.218 --> 29:47.453
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM,
MA'AM?

29:47.453 --> 29:49.021
I'M WORRIED
ABOUT MY NEIGHBOR.

29:49.021 --> 29:50.222
HE'S ELDERLY,
AND I CHECK IN ON HIM,

29:50.222 --> 29:52.091
BUT TODAY THERE'S NO ANSWER.

29:52.091 --> 29:54.560
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU SAW HIM?
THIS MORNING
AROUND 11:00.

29:54.560 --> 29:56.628
I LOOKED THROUGH THE WINDOW,
COULD HEAR THE MUSIC,

29:56.628 --> 29:59.798
BUT THE AIR-CONDITIONING
IS NOT ON, AND IT'S BEEN SO HOT.

29:59.798 --> 30:01.367
WHAT'S HIS NAME?
LARRY.

30:05.637 --> 30:08.540
LARRY. POLICE.

30:08.540 --> 30:10.142
[ DOORKNOB RATTLES ]

30:17.649 --> 30:19.318
[ DOG BARKING ]

30:19.318 --> 30:21.921
MA'AM?
ANYONE IN THE BACK HOUSE?

30:21.921 --> 30:23.589
NO.

30:32.331 --> 30:34.566
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

30:34.566 --> 30:37.269
LARRY! POLICE!

30:42.841 --> 30:45.044
LARRY!

30:45.044 --> 30:47.213
[ RECORD PLAYER CLICKING ]

31:36.795 --> 31:39.031
WHAT?

31:40.666 --> 31:42.334
[ SCOFFS ]

31:42.334 --> 31:46.772
SO WHAT IF SOME GANGSTER
HAD TO TAKE THE FALL?

31:46.772 --> 31:50.042
I DID WHAT I HAD TO DO
TO GET MINE.

31:50.042 --> 31:52.979
WE GOT TO GET OURS, RIGHT?

31:59.485 --> 32:03.155
YOU THINK I DISGRACED
THE DEPARTMENT.

32:05.224 --> 32:07.426
THEY SAY
THEY HAVE YOUR BACK,

32:07.426 --> 32:09.561
BUT THEY WILL THROW YOU
UNDER THE BUS

32:09.561 --> 32:11.863
FASTER THAN ANYONE.

32:11.863 --> 32:16.202
IT'S THE PRESSURES AND THE
FUTILITY OF THE JOB, YOU KNOW?

32:17.569 --> 32:19.638
AND FOR WHAT?

32:19.638 --> 32:22.108
SOME CRAPPY PENSION?

32:22.108 --> 32:24.643
THEN I GOT TO WORK SECURITY
AT CVS.

32:26.979 --> 32:30.249
I DON'T HAVE A SECOND ACT
IN ME!

32:32.518 --> 32:38.657
THE MORTGAGE,
THE CREDIT CARDS, TOYS...

32:38.657 --> 32:42.194
GOT WORSE WHEN THEY TOOK AWAY
OUR OVERTIME.

32:44.663 --> 32:47.599
I WAS GONNA LOSE MY FAMILY.

32:51.470 --> 32:54.606
WHAT?

32:54.606 --> 32:57.843
YOU THINK
YOU'RE BETTER THAN ME?

32:57.843 --> 33:01.113
HUH?

33:01.113 --> 33:04.083
YOU KNOW I AM.

33:06.152 --> 33:10.422
John: THAT THING
WITH THE OLD GUY...

33:10.422 --> 33:13.692
WE WERE JUST DOING
OUR JOBS.

33:13.692 --> 33:17.563
WE DIDN'T KNOW
HE WAS GONNA TAKE IT THAT FAR.

33:17.563 --> 33:20.566
WHEN WE MAKE...

33:20.566 --> 33:25.437
WE MAKE CONTACT WITH PEOPLE,
TAKE CARE OF BUSINESS...

33:27.373 --> 33:29.775
CAN'T TAKE RESPONSIBILITY
FOR WHAT HAPPENS TO THEM

33:29.775 --> 33:31.643
AFTER WE LEAVE.

33:31.643 --> 33:34.913
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

33:34.913 --> 33:37.483
YOU DON'T HAVE TO CONVINCE ME,
SIR.

33:41.087 --> 33:42.554
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]

33:42.554 --> 33:44.990
John: WHOA! LOOK AT THIS GUY.
LIGHT 'EM UP.

33:44.990 --> 33:47.659
[ SIREN WAILS ]

33:55.000 --> 33:56.635
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

33:56.635 --> 33:59.037
[ HORN HONKS ]

34:02.608 --> 34:03.742
SIR, CAN I HAVE -- OH!

34:03.742 --> 34:05.577
[ GUNSHOTS ]

34:05.577 --> 34:06.712
[ GUN CLICKS ]

34:12.951 --> 34:14.686
SHOTS FIRED! OFFICER DOWN!

34:14.686 --> 34:16.255
[ GUNSHOTS ]

34:16.255 --> 34:17.989
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

34:17.989 --> 34:19.825
[ GUN CLICKS ]

34:24.930 --> 34:26.965
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

34:26.965 --> 34:28.700
STEELE!

34:32.104 --> 34:33.572
STEELE!

34:36.007 --> 34:38.477
STEELE!

34:41.747 --> 34:43.682
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

34:44.983 --> 34:46.585
[ SIREN WAILS ]

34:59.598 --> 35:00.799
THANKS.

35:03.235 --> 35:05.371
[ DISTANT SIREN WAILS ]

35:11.277 --> 35:13.512
[ SIGHS ]

35:21.953 --> 35:23.989
I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE THINKING.

35:23.989 --> 35:26.525
AND I'M NOT A COWARD.

35:26.525 --> 35:30.296
I SURVIVED TWO TOURS
IN AFGHANISTAN.

35:30.296 --> 35:32.130
AND, HELL,
AT LEAST OVER THERE,

35:32.130 --> 35:34.166
WE WERE --
WE WERE MAKING PROGRESS.

35:34.166 --> 35:37.936
ALL WE'RE DOING HERE
IS DISPERSING CRIME.

35:37.936 --> 35:39.238
PEOPLE HATE YOU.

35:39.238 --> 35:42.641
LIKE THAT LADY
IN THE ICE-CREAM SHOP, MAN.

35:44.410 --> 35:46.245
WE'RE
ALL JUST NUMBERS HERE,

35:46.245 --> 35:48.247
AND WHY WOULD I RISK MY LIFE
FOR THIS?

35:48.247 --> 35:51.850
YOU HAVE TO BE CRAZY
TO WANT THIS JOB.

35:51.850 --> 35:54.386
IT'S NOT WORTH DYING FOR.

35:56.788 --> 35:58.790
I WAS THINKING ABOUT MY WIFE
AND KIDS.

35:58.790 --> 36:02.828
COULDN'T GET KILLED NOW.
THEY -- THEY JUST GOT ME BACK.

36:15.641 --> 36:18.410
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
CONVINCE ME.

36:27.018 --> 36:29.154
[ SIGHS ]

36:29.154 --> 36:31.223
[ WHISTLES ]

36:31.223 --> 36:33.392
A NICE LITTLE SHINER
IN THE MORNING.

36:33.392 --> 36:35.126
YEAH, I KNOW.

36:35.126 --> 36:37.796
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

36:37.796 --> 36:38.797
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

36:38.797 --> 36:40.165
YOU KNOW,
I THINK I'M GONNA PASS

36:40.165 --> 36:41.367
ON THAT BIRTHDAY THING
TONIGHT.

36:41.367 --> 36:43.302
NAH, YOU SHOULD GO.

36:43.302 --> 36:45.871
MM, NEED TO FINISH
THIS PAPERWORK UP.

36:45.871 --> 36:46.938
I'LL DO IT.

36:46.938 --> 36:49.375
SERIOUSLY?!

36:50.809 --> 36:53.812
OKAY.

36:53.812 --> 36:55.180
THANK YOU.

36:55.180 --> 37:00.719
YOU KNOW, THEY SAY GUINNESS
IS GOOD FOR MILK PRODUCTION

37:00.719 --> 37:03.054
IN CASE
YOU WANT TO RECONSIDER.

37:03.054 --> 37:04.055
I'M NOT.

37:04.055 --> 37:05.223
[ LAUGHS ]

37:05.223 --> 37:06.792
THANKS AGAIN.

37:06.792 --> 37:08.394
HAVE FUN.

37:10.462 --> 37:14.099
NOT LOOKING GOOD
FOR LI'L DEWAIN.

37:14.099 --> 37:17.436
HEY.
DID YOU HEAR WHAT I SAID?

37:17.436 --> 37:20.672
IT'S THE WAY THINGS GO,
MAN.

37:20.672 --> 37:21.840
MEANING WHAT?

37:21.840 --> 37:24.242
BIG DEWAIN HASN'T EXACTLY BEEN
A ROLE MODEL.

37:24.242 --> 37:25.811
SO, WHAT?

37:25.811 --> 37:27.613
WITH A GANGSTER DAD, YOU'RE
SAYING THE POOR KID IS DOOMED?

37:27.613 --> 37:29.581
AND THAT'S REALLY THE WAY
YOU SEE THINGS?

37:29.581 --> 37:31.383
[ SCOFFS ] IT'S WHAT WE SEE
OUT HERE EVERY DAY.

37:31.383 --> 37:33.184
YOU GONNA SAY IT ISN'T?
THAT'S MESSED UP, MAN.

37:33.184 --> 37:34.553
YEAH, IT IS.

37:34.553 --> 37:39.358
IT WAS A BULLSHIT WARRANT,
BUT YOU HAD TO PUSH IT.

37:39.358 --> 37:43.128
WE ASKED A GUY
A QUESTION. HE LIED.

37:43.128 --> 37:44.696
WE BELIEVED HIM.

37:44.696 --> 37:47.833
THAT KID GOT SHOT BECAUSE WE PUT
THE HEAT ON DEWAIN TO SNITCH.

37:47.833 --> 37:50.336
I FEEL LIKE CRAP
ABOUT IT.

37:50.336 --> 37:51.837
I'M WONDERING
WHY YOU DON'T.

37:51.837 --> 37:54.239
IT'S NOT MY FAULT THE ASSHOLE
CHOSE TO BE A GANGSTER.

37:54.239 --> 37:55.741
EVERYONE MAKES CHOICES.

37:55.741 --> 37:58.176
IT'S REALLY EASY TO GET SUCKED
INTO BAD STUFF, HUH?

37:58.176 --> 37:59.645
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

38:01.647 --> 38:03.982
WHAT'S YOUR FUCKING PROBLEM?
LOOK AT MENDOZA.

38:03.982 --> 38:06.318
YOU KNOW, BEING A COP
DOESN'T CHANGE WHO YOU ARE

38:06.318 --> 38:07.853
OR MAKE YOU
A BETTER PERSON.

38:07.853 --> 38:09.020
WHOSE SIDE ARE YOU ON?

38:09.020 --> 38:10.956
WE'RE HERE BECAUSE YOUR HOMEBOY
MENDOZA LIED!

38:10.956 --> 38:12.090
I DIDN'T KNOW HE WAS LYING.

38:12.090 --> 38:13.659
I WAS DOING MY JOB,
WHICH, AT THE TIME,

38:13.659 --> 38:15.260
WAS TO GO AFTER THE GUYS
WHO WENT AFTER ONE OF US.

38:15.260 --> 38:19.665
THIS WAS NEVER ABOUT MENDOZA.
THIS WAS ALWAYS ABOUT YOU.

38:31.209 --> 38:33.311
[ SIGHS ]

38:42.988 --> 38:44.590
[ SIGHS ]

38:53.231 --> 38:54.866
YOU'RE BACK AGAIN.

38:54.866 --> 38:56.201
SORRY ABOUT EARLIER.

38:56.201 --> 38:57.669
WELL...

38:57.669 --> 39:00.739
YOU WERE PRETTY RUDE.

39:00.739 --> 39:03.241
HOPE I DIDN'T HURT
YOUR FEELINGS.

39:03.241 --> 39:04.342
NO, YOU DIDN'T.

39:04.342 --> 39:06.111
MAYBE A LITTLE BIT.

39:06.111 --> 39:09.347
WHAT'S IN THE, UH, BOX?

39:09.347 --> 39:11.417
CUPCAKES.
IT'S A NEW RECIPE.

39:11.417 --> 39:14.019
OH, YEAH?

39:14.019 --> 39:17.188
WHAT ARE THE BLUE ONES?

39:17.188 --> 39:18.189
[ LAUGHTER ]

39:18.189 --> 39:19.558
OH, MY GOSH. OH!

39:19.558 --> 39:22.127
REMEMBER CRAZY-ASS RENATA
FROM SOUTHWEST DIVISION?

39:22.127 --> 39:23.562
Man: OH, YEAH.

39:23.562 --> 39:25.163
[ LAUGHS ] ONE DAY,
I'M HOOKING HER UP, RIGHT?

39:25.163 --> 39:28.667
SO, I HAVE MY ARMS ON HER WRIST,
BUT MY HANDS KEEP SLIPPING OFF.

39:28.667 --> 39:29.968
OOH!

39:29.968 --> 39:32.270
AND I'M LIKE, "RENATA,
WHAT'S THIS ON YOUR WRIST?"

39:32.270 --> 39:35.541
SHE SAYS, "I JUST GOT FINISHED
HAVING SEX WITH BOB BEVERLY."

39:35.541 --> 39:37.242
[ LAUGHTER ]

39:37.242 --> 39:40.011
I MUST HAVE WENT THROUGH, LIKE,
SIX BOTTLES OF HAND SANITIZER.

39:40.011 --> 39:43.949
OH, A BIRTHDAY CAKE!
A BURGER CAKE!

39:43.949 --> 39:45.216
[ LAUGHTER ]

39:45.216 --> 39:48.086
HAVE SOME SLIDERS.
WHY DO THEY CALL 'EM SLIDERS?

39:48.086 --> 39:49.655
OH, WHOA. OH.

40:13.211 --> 40:15.681
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

40:22.253 --> 40:24.723
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

40:26.458 --> 40:28.460
[ BABY COOING ]

40:42.140 --> 40:43.742
[ GASPS ]

40:47.713 --> 40:51.517
[ Voice breaking ] NO.

40:51.517 --> 40:53.485
NO.

40:53.485 --> 40:56.087
[ SOBBING ]

40:58.256 --> 41:00.592
OH, NO.

41:13.972 --> 41:17.142
NO.
